title: U.A.W. Threatens Strikes at More Plants
description: The United Auto Workers union said workers would walk out of more plants on Friday if it didn’t make progress in talks with General Motors, Ford and Stellantis.

title: Max to Stream Pro Sports Starting in October
description: Media companies are racing to figure out how to merge live sporting events with their popular but still cash-bleeding streaming services.

title: Instacart Soars 40% as It Begins Trading, an Encouraging Sign for Tech I.P.O.s
description: Shares opened at $42 on Tuesday, valuing the grocery delivery company at $13.9 billion.

title: Billions to Connect Everyone to High-Speed Internet Could Still Fall Short
description: President Biden has promised to provide every American access to reliable high-speed internet. But some have raised concerns about whether the funds will achieve all of the administration’s goals.

title: Sam Bankman-Fried’s Parents Sued by FTX
description: The lawyers overseeing the bankrupt cryptocurrency exchange accused Joe Bankman and Barbara Fried of enriching themselves with money their son stole from customers.

title: YouTube Blocks Russell Brand From Making Money on Its Platform
description: The comedian’s channel has over six million followers, but he will be unable to draw income from advertising around his videos.

title: Google Connects A.I. Chatbot Bard to YouTube, Gmail and More Facts
description: Google hopes that giving its chatbot more capabilities and improving its accuracy will give more users a reason to use it.

title: In Lies of P, Pinocchio Takes No Prisoners
description: Lies of P, from a studio targeting fans of Bloodborne, Sekiro and the Dark Souls series, traces an arduous journey to end a puppet rebellion.

title: Strike Is a High-Stakes Gamble for Autoworkers and the Labor Movement
description: Experts on unions and the industry said the U.A.W. strike could accelerate a wave of worker actions, or stifle labor’s recent momentum
